NPM (Node package Manager)

npm calls the reusable code a package

package is a folder contains javascript code

modules/ dependencies/ package  are all the same and use interchangeably (shared javascript code)




//Local dependency - only use the package only for this particular project

//npm i <packageName>


//Global dependency - use it in every project

//npm install -g <packageName>
//sudo install -g <packageName> (mac)



npm init (step by step creation for package.json)
npm inti -y (everything default)
